<recipe>
<title>
Whole Wheat Neiman Marcus $250 Chocolate Chip Cookie Recipe
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 cup butter at cool room temperature
1 1/2 cups brown sugar packed
1/2 cup granulated sugar
2 large eggs
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
3 cups rolled oats
1 1/3 cups all-purpose flour
1/2 cup whole wheat flour
1/2 teaspoon kosher salt
1 teaspoon baking powder
1 teaspoon baking soda
1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon
2 cups mini semisweet chocolate chips
1 cup finely chopped walnuts optional
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 375 F. Line two baking sheets with parchment paper or silicone baking mats.
Measure oats into a blender or food processor, and then blend to a fine powder. Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugars.
Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix together flours, ground oats, salt, baking powder, baking soda, and cinnamon.
Stir dry ingredients into creamed butter and sugar.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by 1.5 tablespoon scoops onto prepared cookie sheets, spacing about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 8-12 minutes, or until middles are set and edges are light golden brown.
</instructions>
</recipe>
